<item>
            <title>[DIGESTER-125] Memory leak in Digester class by inputSources collection </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DIGESTER-125</link>
                <project id="12310471" key="DIGESTER">Commons Digester</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is no clean method for inputSources list from Digeste class, &lt;br/&gt;
in frequent usage of parse() method inputSources collection will collect references to sources objects. In this situation the number of object references represented by sources from inputSources,&lt;br/&gt;
will be increased and consume a lot of memory. For intensive parsing smth around 200 mb for 8 hours was consumed.&lt;br/&gt;
Solution is simple method cleanup() should contain line inputSources.clear(); at the end of the method.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
